@startuml MatchMonitor_DataLineage
title Match Monitor Page - Data Lineage & Dependencies

skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor<<BackgroundJob>> #FFE4B5
    BackgroundColor<<Database>> #E8F5E9
    BackgroundColor<<WebPage>> #E3F2FD
    BackgroundColor<<ExternalDB>> #FFF9C4
}

skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FFFACD
    BorderColor #F0E68C
}

!define CLOUDBLUE #E3F2FD
!define JOBCOLOR #FFE4B5
!define DBCOLOR #E8F5E9
!define WEBCOLOR #E3F2FD

' Background Jobs Section
package "Background Jobs (Scheduled)" {
    rectangle "MatchMonitorClassification\nBySport\n(md/BySport)" <<BackgroundJob>> as JobBySport
    note right of JobBySport
        **Run Frequency**: Every 5 minutes
        **Purpose**: Detect group betting by sport
        **Processing**:
        - Scan matches by sport type
        - Detect suspicious betting patterns
        - Classify customers as PA
        - Assign specific CC categories
    end note
    
    rectangle "MatchMonitorClassification\n(General)\n(md/General)" <<BackgroundJob>> as JobGeneral
    note right of JobGeneral
        **Run Frequency**: Every 5 minutes
        **Purpose**: General match monitoring
        **Processing**:
        - Cross-sport detection
        - Multi-bettype analysis
        - Customer classification (CC)
        - Problem Account marking
        - One match at a time (FIFO queue)
    end note
}

' Database Tables Section
package "Database (MySQL - CTS_DataCenter)" {
    database "CTSMatchMonitor" <<Database>> as TableMatch
    note right of TableMatch
        **Primary Table**
        - MatchID (PK)
        - SportType, BetTypeID, BetID
        - Market, Reason
        - IsVerified, VerifiedBy
        - FraudTrans (comma-separated)
        - FraudRefno (parlay)
        - EventDate, ScanDate
        - TicketType (Single/Parlay)
    end note
    
    database "CTSCustomerClassification" <<Database>> as TableCust
    note right of TableCust
        **Customer CC Table**
        - CustID (PK)
        - CategoryID (CC type)
        - CategoryName
        - SportGroupID
        - IsPA (Problem Account)
        - ProbationEndDate
        - LastModifiedDate
    end note
    
    database "CTSMatchMonitorDetail" <<Database>> as TableDetail
    note right of TableDetail
        **Match Detail**
        - ID (PK), MatchID (FK)
        - CustID, TransID
        - Refno (parlay)
        - BetChoice
        - VerifiedBy, VerifiedDate
    end note
}

package "Database (SQL Server - bodb_VR2Model)" {
    database "Match Info\n(MainDB)" <<ExternalDB>> as MainDB
    note right of MainDB
        **Match Master Data**
        - MatchID
        - HomeName, AwayName
        - LeagueName
        - KickOffTime
        - MatchSection
        - DataSource
    end note
    
    database "Transaction\n(MainDB)" <<ExternalDB>> as TransDB
    note right of TransDB
        **Betting Transactions**
        - TransID, Refno
        - CustID
        - BetAmount, BetChoice
        - TransDate, IsVoid
    end note
}

' Web Page Section
package "Web Application (ASP.NET MVC)" {
    rectangle "Match Monitor Page\n(Website/MatchMonitor)" <<WebPage>> as WebPage
    note bottom of WebPage
        **Main Features**:
        1. **Search Matches**: Display dangerous matches
        2. **View Details**: Show fraudulent tickets
        3. **Verify Trans**: PIC verify suspicious bets
        4. **Association Detection**: Manual group detection
        5. **Mark PA**: Mark customers as Problem Account
        6. **Export Excel**: Export match analysis
        
        **User Roles**:
        - Monitor Team: View & verify
        - Host Team: Full control (Hold Key, Mark PA)
    end note
}

' Data Flow - Write Operations (Jobs → Database)
JobBySport -down-> TableMatch : **INSERT/UPDATE**\n(Write Match Detection)
JobBySport -down-> TableDetail : **INSERT**\n(Write Fraud Tickets)
JobBySport -down-> TableCust : **UPDATE**\n(Classify Customer CC)

JobGeneral -down-> TableMatch : **INSERT/UPDATE**\n(Write Match Detection)
JobGeneral -down-> TableDetail : **INSERT**\n(Write Fraud Tickets)
JobGeneral -down-> TableCust : **UPDATE**\n(Classify Customer CC)

note on link
    **Data Written by Jobs**:
    1. Detected matches → CTSMatchMonitor
    2. Fraud ticket list → CTSMatchMonitorDetail
    3. Customer classification → CTSCustomerClassification
    
    **Classification Logic**:
    - Match has multiple tickets
    - Job runs detection rules
    - If rules satisfied:
      * CustID with ticket is marked as CC (PA)
      * Assign specific CC category
      * Update customer classification
end note

' Data Flow - Read Operations (Database → Web Page)
TableMatch -down-> WebPage : **SELECT**\n(Read Match List)
TableDetail -down-> WebPage : **SELECT**\n(Read Ticket Details)
TableCust -down-> WebPage : **SELECT**\n(Read Customer CC Info)
MainDB -down-> WebPage : **SELECT**\n(Read Match Info)
TransDB -down-> WebPage : **SELECT**\n(Read All Tickets)

note on link
    **Stored Procedures Used**:
    
    **Main Page**:
    - CTS_DC_MatchMonitor_Get
      → Get matches by scan/event date
      → Filter by sport, bettype, reason
      → Join with CTSCustomerClassification
    
    **Detail Page**:
    - CTS_DC_MatchMonitorDetail_Get
      → Get fraud tickets for match
      → Include customer CC info
    - CTS_Rpt_MatchMonitor_MatchInfo
      → Get match details from MainDB
      → HomeName, AwayName, League, etc.
    - CTS_Rpt_MatchMonitor_AllTickets_Get
      → Get all tickets (not just fraud)
      → From MainDB Transaction table
end note

' Cross-References
note right of JobBySport
    **Cross-Reference**:
    📂 md/BySport/MatchMonitorClassificationBySport
    
    **Related Flows**:
    - Detection rules by sport
    - Category assignment logic
    - Push to external systems
end note

note right of JobGeneral
    **Cross-Reference**:
    📂 md/General/MatchMonitorClassification
    ✅ **Status**: Flow chart đã tạo
    
    **Key Features**:
    - FIFO queue (one match at a time)
    - 2 jobs: UpdateStatus + Classify
    - General detection rules
    - Cross-sport analysis
    - Push to MainDB included
end note

' Data Freshness
note bottom of TableMatch
    **Data Freshness**:
    - **Match data**: 5 minutes (job frequency)
    - **Customer CC**: Real-time (updated by jobs)
    - **Match info**: Real-time (from MainDB)
    - **Transaction data**: Real-time (from MainDB)
    
    **Data Latency**:
    - Web page shows data with max 5-min delay
    - Depends on background job execution
end note

' Key Concepts
note top of TableCust
    **Customer Classification (CC)**:
    
    **Concept**:
    - CC = Customer Class = Problem Account category
    - Each customer can have specific CC type
    - CC assigned based on betting behavior
    
    **Flow**:
    1. MatchID has multiple tickets
    2. Background job runs detection
    3. If rules satisfied:
       → CustID with ticket → marked as CC (PA)
       → Assign specific CC category
       → Example: "Group Betting", "Sharp Player", etc.
    
    **Categories**:
    - Normal, PotentialPA, PA, Probation
    - Sport-specific classifications
    - Risk level indicators
end note

@enduml

